<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Settings Menu Requirement</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Notes</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>TV settings are either adjusted from All Settings menu on the TV using t=
he IR remote or from the SmartCast Mobile app.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All settings, also known as the sidebar.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When SmartCast Mobile app is used to adjust settings, the order is the s=
ame as in the All Settings menu displayed on the TV.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Differences are only as required for settings as per limitation of the a=
pp.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When a system setting is changed using SmartCast Mobile app, a notificat=
ion displays confirming the change has been completed with exception that c=
hanges to most parental control settings do NOT display a notification on t=
he TV.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When SmartCast Mobile app is used to adjust the value of a slider, the a=
djustment is also annunciated on the TV with a slider (no notification in t=
his case). &nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When the MENU or gear key is first pressed, the header for the menu is A=
ll Settings.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The default selected setting is the top setting (Picture) if no selectio=
n previously made. Thereafter All Settings launches with the last used sett=
ing selected.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">7</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All Settings Timeout and Dismissal:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>For all skus, after the last key press timer starts. After 1 minute of s=
creen quiescence the sidebar is dismissed.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>During one 1 minute timer, if another key press the restart the 1 minute=
 timer.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Antenna Scan complete then 1 minute timer starts.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>A key press that displays another UI takes down the sidebar including:</=
p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>INPUT, PIC, MIC, HOME, partner keys</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"m1vp1qukje">PIC key dismisses Quick and deep links=
 to Picture mode.</span></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>no dismissal with VOLUME, MUTE keys, INFO or CC</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"tjgvpidnpj">INFO displays the input change control=
 which displays concurrently with sidebar (no overlap)</span></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>For System Info after 5 minutes timer then sidebar is dismissed.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"l76y2k7v90">Sidebar timeout timer is paused during=
 if Talk Back is voicing, restarts after Talk Back is quiet.</span></p></li=
>
<li>
<p>No timeout with antenna scan</p></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1 minute timeout does not apply:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>During antenna scan.</p></li>
<li>
<p>System Info (system info timeout after 5 minutes).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Hidden menu</p></li>
<li>
<p>non-customer facing ODM/SOC menus including factory menus</p></li>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"ffsjo8jcw5">Talk Back voicing</span></p></li>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"snx6crfmv1">CC notifications and closed captions d=
o not take down TV settings.</span></p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">8</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If a setting, option or name exceeds the maximum of 15 characters for in=
put name or 24 characters for TV name or does not fit then ellipses used to=
 indicate the name is incomplete. <span data-colorid=3D"pfzkjwgii6"> </span=
></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">9</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span data-colorid=3D"lvi0bnqdey">If Loki has not received values from D=
TV service the first time leave setting blank (not a 0). </span></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span data-colorid=3D"om89gve1yp">This applies to Quick menu and All set=
tings.</span></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-2AllSettingsMenu-2.1AllSettingsMenuOrder">2.1 All Settings Men=
u Order</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"6b=
4727f3-ad04-47e3-a27b-a5a0acd2180e" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col style=3D"width: 220.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 496.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Sub menu</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Definition</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Picture</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures the picture settings.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Audio</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures the audio settings.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>HDMI &amp; Gaming</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures HDMI, CEC and gaming settings.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Network</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures and tests the network connection for the TV.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Bluetooth and Remote</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures Bluetooth Headphones, game controllers and the Voice remote.<=
/p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Antenna Channels</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures the tuner.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">7</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Accessibility</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures closed captions, video description, talk back and zoom mode f=
or all models with SmartCast TV.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">8</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>System</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures menu language, time and timers, TV and input names, power mod=
e, parental controls including the System PIN, store demo. Includes access =
to System Information and reset to defaults.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">9</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Support</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Provides support including access to the support code, reboot TV, and ch=
eck for updates. &nbsp;Includes a QR code for the user manual.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">10</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Privacy and Legal</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Configures viewing data and DAI settings. Displays the VIZIO privacy pol=
icy and the License List. &nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
