<h2 id=3D"id-2AllSettingsMenu-2.2NavigationofAllSettings">2.2 Navigation of=
 All Settings</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"20=
313c01-b22e-4f19-9628-94b818b5a05c" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col style=3D"width: 452.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 264.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Definition</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Notes</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A highlighted setting can be changed in two ways</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A press of the LEFT/RIGHT keys toggles the options displayed right of th=
e setting in the the sidebar menu.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Setting is immediately changed.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A press of UP/DOWN navigates up and down in a menu.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A press of Up at top setting wraps to bottom setting. Examples:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Picture in All Settings wraps to Privacy &amp; Legal Central</p></li>
<li>
<p>Picture header in Picture menu wraps to Picture Mode Edit???</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>A press of Down at bottom setting wraps to top setting. Examples:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Privacy &amp; Legal Central in All Settings wraps to Picture</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Alternatively, a press of OK key opens the specific setting.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The setting name becomes the menu header</p></li>
<li>
<p>options displayed in the menu below.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The first option is selected &amp; highlighted.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>A press of the UP or DOWN key highlights the next option above or below.=
</p></li>
<li>
<p>To change to the highlighted setting press OK key.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The setting menu closes and the originating menu reopens with the settin=
g and new option highlighted.</p></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>For example, in Picture menu,</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Picture mode is highlighted</p></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>
<p>press of OK key opens the Picture Mode options menu</p></li>
<li>
<p>current picture mode option highlighted</p></li>
<li>
<p>A press of the DOWN key highlights the next picture mode.</p></li>
<li>
<p>A press of OK switches to the highlighted option</p></li>
<li>
<p>Returns to the Picture menu with Picture mode highlighted.</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If a carat is displayed the corresponding arrow navigates:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Left carat for header, then left arrow key takes back to All Settings ma=
in menu</p></li>
<li>
<p>Right carat for a setting, then right arrow opens the menu for the setti=
ng</p></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>For example,</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Picture highlighted with left carat, left arrow returns to main menu wit=
h Picture highlighted.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Advanced settings highlighted with right carat, right arrow opens Advanc=
ed Settings submenu</p></li>
<li>
<p>Input Name highlighted with right carat, right arrow opens the Input Nam=
e with soft keyboard.</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Under specific conditions, if a setting is noted as =E2=80=9Cnot availab=
le=E2=80=9D, then the setting cannot be selected or used.&nbsp; The setting=
 is grayed out and not sent to the SmartCast app until the condition is rel=
ieved.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Gray out is not used in SmartCast mobile (setting is not displayed).</p>
<p>Gray out is not used in Set and Forget settings (e.g. Digital Audio unde=
r TV Channels).</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
